messages.title: Standing Up for Real Change
messages.content: I joined UKIP to oppose "New Labour" which had virtually no policies that benefited the country but were keen on restricting our freedom. I see their replacements continuing the trend.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Targets set on energy consumption have been missed by miles.
Policies on immigration have long term consequences for environment, public services and employment.
The quantity of residential development imposed on us is a symptom of failure.
